4.94/5  rDev +12.3%look: 5 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 5The pinnacle of a hefeweizen. One of the best beers I've ever had the full exceeds and raises the bar of what to expect with a hefe.
A - Pours a golden, honey color with a full, 3 finger head. Incredible head retention that never fully goes away. 
S -  Powerful and to the point. Banana and cloves. Not much else to say aside from an incredible aroma; no hidden subtleties. 
T - The taste follows perfectly in line with the aroma. Optimal blend of bitterness and sweetness, leaving a lingering, banana aftertaste. Perfect match for my personal tastes.
M - Crisp, incredibly smooth and drinkable with the perfect amount of carbonation. Medium - full bodied beer.
O - As close to perfect a beer you'll find. As a big fan of hefeweizen's, I was estatic to finally get a hold of this beer. My expectations were well surpassed. From the moment you start pouring and as the aromas dissipate in the air around you; to the last sip, this beer will not let you down. Only downside - it's now going to be hard to find something that'll compare. Will be stocking the fridge. 1,068 charactersZaktcc, May 11, 2016
