4.08/5  rDev -7.3%look: 4 | smell: 4 | taste: 4.25 | feel: 3.75 |  overall: 4My 7th beer rated from this monastic brewery's 21 offerings on BA, so I think I've got a good sense of them.
It Looks like a hefe, but probably a little clearer and I got a big rocky head that dissipated. 
Smells somehow lacked that classic banana I most like from the style. 
Taste is balanced, the fruits and sweet wheat are kept in check with a healthy dose of hops.
Feel tells me the hops dosage is too healthy. Dry is OK, but this verges on bitter.
Overall, that bitter makes it difficult to go with food. Refreshing, yes. Food needs some sweeter malt in there for me.
Listed on the "1001", it probably very much deserves this... although I'm not a fan of spicy hefes.
Reviewed also in Roger Protz' CAMRA classic "300 Beers To Try Before You Die!" 753 charactersBeginner2, May 01, 2016
