4.44/5  rDev +0.9%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5I love wheat beers and this is a gem.
Cloudy, golden, yellow colour with huge, dense head that recedes slowly to a 1mm white cap. Some lacing.
The nose is quite subtle for a wheat beer. Plenty of spice and citrus but not overwhelming.
Tons of wheat, yeast, clove & citrus but perfectly balanced and eminently drinkable. So smooth. So refreshing.
Awesome mouthfeel. Coats the tongue. Slight prickle.
A fabulous beer. Excellent in the summer served straight from the fridge and, served a tad warmer, it also makes for a big, spicy hit on a wet, dark day in January. 568 charactersSpike, Dec 03, 2015
