Banana, clove, you know the deal with a Hefeweizen. What sets this apart is the execution. Beautiful mouthfeel, great fruity chew to it. Carbonation is perfect, looks like a dream in the glass. Head is abundant and lasts a good long while. Improves as it warms up, which is true of almost no American versions of this style. People who swear off the hef because they've never had a proper Bavarian need to better educate their palates before calling it a day. 655 charactersdd43, Jul 26, 2015
