4.24/5  rDev -3.6%look: 5 | smell: 4 | taste: 4.25 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.25Poured from a 12oz bottle into a mug because unfortunately I don't have a weizen glass.
A: Pours a picture perfect cloudy golden color with a dense, creamy, 2 finger head of white foam. After a minute or 2 the foam settles to a crown that caps the beer perfectly. A decent amount of lacing is left clinging to the sides of the glass. 
S: Aromas of clove and baked banana bread, with a good amount of spice. Some fruity yeast esters and biscuity malts also coming out. A hint of white pepper as the beer warms. 
T: There is a refreshing flavor of clove and banana bread with a light spiciness. Biscuity malts and a faint amount of fruity yeast esters. This beer has a somewhat strong phenolic character. 
M: Light bodied with high carbonation and a crisp, refreshing mouthfeel. Semi dry on the finish.
O: Overall I thought this was a good beer with interesting flavors of clove and banana. It was crisp and refreshing, and would be a nice thirst quencher on a hot summer day. This could be a pretty versatile beer to pair with a variety of different foods. I would surely drink this again. 1,093 charactersTheItalianStallion, Jul 26, 2015
