4.54/5  rDev +3.2%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5Poured from a pint bottle.
A: Pours a murky golden honey color with two fingers of frothy white head. Retention is insane, lacing is prominent and incredibly beautiful.
S: Sweet malts, banana, clove, honey, white pepper, wheat, apple, a slight citrus, and some grassy earthy hops.
T: Sweet malts, sweet bread, clove. banana, honey, citrus, herbal spices, and earthy hops. This is what a Hefeweizen should taste like.
M: Light bodied, mid-to high carbonation, incredibly smooth. Truly enjoyable to drink.
O: An absolute world-class phenomenal brew. The best Hefeweizen I have had so far. I highly recommend this beer to every BA. I have definitely earned my frequent drinker miles on this German classic. 708 charactersCannibalgasm, Jul 05, 2015
4.32/5  rDev -1.8%look: 4.25 | smell: 4 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4 |  overall: 4.5Beerbom, Jul 05, 2015
4.26/5  rDev -3.2%look: 5 | smell: 4 | taste: 4.25 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.25Pours a beautiful, hazy, sunny, peach pulp color, with a dense, stable head.
Smells of ripe banana, red apple skin, together with grassy hops and white pepper. Banana shines through beautifully, while balanced by the hops and a coppery whiff, remaining the beers enjoyable balance.
Drinks incredibly smooth, carried by soft yeast, feels utmost silk on the palate, while providing enough carbonation to create an refreshing impression. 
Begins with cakey malts, clove, honey and a fantastic yeast smoothness, establishing the beers world-class mouthfeel. While the spices are prominent, they do get tamed by earth, a glimpse of oak and the grassy, slightly herbal hops. Finishes with young banana, more clove and honey, while the hops provide a pleasant, refreshing herb presence.
The interplay between noteable carbonation and euro hops turns out great, as the beer don't need no bitter hop punch to balance the sweeter spices, but uses the metallic qualities from the carbonation to create a short, refreshing burn, taming the sweeter ingredients of the brew. As easy as this drinks, as convincing is the beers receipt, showcasing a truly well made Weissbier, which leaves a refreshing, perfectly balanced impression on the palate. 1,236 charactersaleigator, Jul 04, 2015
