4.33/5  rDev -1.6%look: 4.5 | smell: 4 | taste: 4.25 | feel: 5 |  overall: 4.5Pours a murky, golden-yellow color with a white foamy head. Glows a beautiful, radiant golden color when light shines through.  Great retention. Little to no lacing. 
Aroma contains a strong scent of lemon rind, grassiness, and yeast. Reminiscent of fresh grass clippings on a hot summer day. 
Taste is refreshing. Subtle lemon notes and orange zest. A perfect amount of yeast--doesn't dominate but it very present. Hint of bubblegum. Some nice sweet, tartness on the finish.
Mouthfeel is light bodied. Extremely crisp and refreshing. Quite possibly the most drinkable beer I've ever had. I could've chugged this pint in no time. 
Overall, Hefes are typically towards the bottom of my favorites list, but this one did quite a bit to change that. Definitely the best Hefe I've ever had, and one of the better beers I've ever had, period. Great beer, one that even a newbie to craft beer could appreciate, or even a craft veteran. Great for anyone, on any occasion. 967 charactersmajorbase2, May 23, 2015
