4.34/5  rDev -1.4%look: 4 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.25Purchased 500 ml bottle from the health food store for about $3 and poured into a tall beer glass.  A very hazy rich golden-yellow color with a fluffy pure white head that slowly fades leaving slight lacing.  Aroma is of bread, yeast and slight citrus.  Taste is really nice with some citrus and bread followed by a muted cinnamon/nutmeg-like spiciness that really makes the beer.  Towards the bottom of the pint, the beer started to have a slight metallic after-taste, maybe due to the trip across the Atlantic.  Goes down really easy, but is not super thin - enough body to keep you from pounding it, but enough carbonation to keep it refreshing.  Overall, a fantastic wheat beer and a great deal for the price. 713 charactersFFreak, Mar 23, 2015
