5/5  rDev +13.6%look: 5 | smell: 5 | taste: 5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 5Appearance: Very hazy straw color with a huge fluffy head that did not want to go down!
Smell: Very strong yeast smell. Some wheat aroma, but mostly yeast - spicy, citric, nutty.
Taste: Yeast are up front, providing that hard to pin down flavor - banana, citrus, spice, clove, soybean, peanut. Dry wheat malt flavor follows it up. The flavors are strong, but smooth and balanced.
Mouthfeel: The thickness and fine carbonation give this one a very creamy feel. No residual feel.
Overall: I can see why this brewery has been around for so long. All the components of this beer are bold, but well blended. I usually get bored of Hefe’s before finishing 12 onces; this one left me wanting another 16. 702 charactersSensorySupernova, Mar 15, 2015
