4.46/5  rDev +1.4%look: 4.75 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5Pours a cloudy light amber.  World Class head volume, lacing and retention.
Classic wheat nose of light clove and banana, a touch of lemon, yeast and biscuit.  As it warms, a subtle spicy character emerges.
Medium bodied with a very smooth texture that approaches creamy.  Well carbonated with a rich effervescence from the middle on.
This beer is the standard for Hefe Weissbiers and is world class.  The flavor profile is intense, complex and well balanced.  It begins with a mild tartness that separates into lemon and banana.   As these fade in the middle, clove comes forward over a biscuit background with a hint of spice and dryness.  The finish is crisp, with a mild biscuit fading and leaving clove. 711 characterstillmac62, Mar 10, 2015
