4.05/5  rDev -8%look: 4 | smell: 4 | taste: 4 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4500 ml bottle, with no apparent bottled on date present. My first encounter with a bottle of Weihenstephaner.
Poured into a clear balloon snifter.
A - Pours a bit of a darker golden body than expected. Three big fluffy fingers of white head. Some spotty fluffy lacing. Standard appearance, but looks good for what it is.
S - The aroma is simple, yet befitting of the style. Lots of yeasty / clove spiciness.
T - The taste is classic of the style - creamy, yeasty, crisp, bready, floral, and spicy.
 M - The feel is very crisp, clean, and easy-drinking. Light bodied with good carbonation.
Overall, hefeweizens have never been my favorite, but this is clearly a well-executed and refined example of the style. Looking forward to trying more from Weihenstephaner.
Weihenstephaner Hefeweissbier -----4/5. 808 charactersmfnmbvp, Jan 26, 2015
