4.2/5  rDev -4.5%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4 | feel: 4 |  overall: 4.25Around cellar temperature in a weizen glass.
An extremely fluffy two-finger white head sits aloft over a slightly hazy rich golden-straw ale. Lots of carbonation to see. Gorgeous.
The aroma abounds with banana, bread, and yeast. There might even be some peaches, green apples, and mango in there as well. Oh, and cloves.
Its flavor is more straight-forward to me. First I get sweet banana with a touch of the tart fruitiness, then a clean finish of not-too-sweet breadiness. Think soft pretzel or a simple French bread as opposed to the richer white breads associated with holidays.
The carbonation is up there, but not out of control.
Just a really tasty, bready beer with some added complexities that most beers this light don't possess. 744 charactersKuaff, Jun 09, 2014
