4.5/5  rDev +2.3%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5Bought at Lager Mill $3.29
Bottle marked 6383, no other markings, at 45 degrees into a weizen glass
Aroma of yeast and spice
Head large (5 cm), off white, creamy, slowly diminishing to 3 mm layer
Lacing spotty; a few tiny islands of small bubbles
Body medium yellow, cloudy
Flavor begins sweet with coriander and banana predominating with some phenolic yeastiness present. No alcohol, no hops, no diacetyl. Ends lightly sweet with yeast flavor.
Palate medium, creamy, soft carbonation.
A VERY easy drinking beer, sweet enough to make you want more but not cloying. The flavor is subdued enough to make you keep coming back. An excellent hefeweissbier! 653 charactersOzzylizard, May 26, 2014
