4.46/5  rDev +1.4%look: 4.25 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.25 |  overall: 4.5Poured from a bottle into a tulip glass at around 45°F
Appearance: Cloudy golden orange hue; Swirled and poured the last bit which resulted in a two finger white head 
Smell: Banana is dominant with wheat, yeast, and cloves playing in the background. Perhaps some citrus as well
Taste: Starts off with a blast of banana with hints of lemon and fades into a wheaty/yeasty and clove combination that lingers on the palate. 
Mouthfeel: Very light as expected yet extremely smooth and refreshing
Overall: When reviewing wheat beers, many of us on here (including myself) mention that it's not our style, but this is one of my very few exceptions. There's only so much you can do with a hefeweizen, but this one is truly special! And you don't even have to seek it out. Therefore, this is really the only hefe worth buying in my opinion. Stands out among others in the style at a competitive price point. This is one of those beers that make you look forward to summer. It tastes like clove spiced banana bread. The ratings say it all. Cheers! 1,044 charactersBone53, Apr 27, 2014
