 Aroma is robust with malted wheat, lemon rind, banana and a touch of clove, very clean smelling to be sure.
 Taste is just out of this world good, clean wheat flavor with a touch of estery yeast, a slight tartness creeps in, or is that just the very satisfying carbonation? Who cares? this beer is a classic world class beer for very good reasons. It's damn near perfect.
