4.78/5  rDev +8.6%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 5 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.75Who doesn’t like a world class hefe? 
 
Pours a beautiful hazy straw with hints of orange.
 
Smells of powdery yeast, sweet ripe bananas, and a touch of clove.
Taste great.  Just superb.  The crisp powdery hefe is refreshing, with the sweetness and spiciness playing well against each other and some subtle hops rounding out the flavor.
 
Mouthfeel was spot on.  Full but not thick.  The yeast in suspension helps create that illusion of fullness without thickness in my opinion. 
Overall, certainly deserving of its world class status for the Hefes, and I consider this a go to in the summer months when I want to mix it up from the hoppy IPAs.  663 characterstaylor714914, Jun 19, 2013
