4.4/5  rDev 0%look: 4 | smell: 4 | taste: 5 | feel: 4 |  overall: 4Picked this up on a lark based on the recommendation of the beer counter guy in a grocery store of all places. Good job beer guy.
Average hefeweiss beers are a dime a dozen. It's an easy style of make average / okay, a hard style to screw up. But on the flip, it's a hard style to distinguish yourself in it seems.
This is one hell of a beer to stand out. Pours with a towering thunderhead of dense foam into a weiss glass. A hazy golden, with swirling bits of yellow orange yesty goodness.
Smell is nutmeg, clove, vanilla and banana with a nice yeast aroma. 
A subtle sweetness in the mouth. Very smooth. Exceptionally smooth with a nice spiciness and teensy bit of bite. There's some alcohol taste when it warms a bit, which kind of surprises me given the 5.4 abv. 
Fantastic beer. Glad to have tried it. It's so smooth and so true to style that this ought to be the benchark for hefe weissbiers the world over. 
Loved it. This isn't a session beer. It's a drain the bottle and have three more before you even realize what happened beer.
The simplicity of it blows me away. This is one of those beers that should illustrate that yeast doesn't just add fizz and alcohol to a beer, but actually makes the style. 1,218 charactersLiving816, Aug 19, 2012
