4.74/5  rDev +7.7%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.75Poured this into a weizen glass.
A: Pours a cloudy golden yellow color. Huge head takes up about 4 inches of glass. Some lacing is left on the glass after. The head quickly subsides.
S: Smells of banana, clove and a faint hint of bubble gum. Some citrus and wheaty yeast are also picked up upon further sniffing.
T: What a beauty this is. I get some spicy clove and wheat initially. The citrus and banana work together afterwards and there is a slight taste of bubble gum that comes through at the end/aftertaste. This sets the standards for how hefes should taste.
M: Refreshing. I could easily put down a whole sixer of this on a nice summer day. The drinkability is wonderful and it is a medium-bodied brew. 
Overall: Hands down the best hefeweizen in the world. There is no question about it. One of my favorite all time beers and my go-to for the summer months. The balance and drinkability (aside from the taste) is what sets this beer apart from the other hefeweizens. You can drink your pale ales and IPAs in the summer, I'll take a Weihenstephaner Hefeweissbier!! 1,077 charactersRichD, Jul 17, 2012
