4.67/5  rDev +6.1%look: 4 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5Thank god for imports!
Weihenstephaner Hefeweissbier is an instant favorite. Coming from the "oldest brewery in the world" it should be no surprise that this beer is crafted to perfection.
I bought this in a "Beers of the World" 10-pack from World Market hoping to expand my taste profile. WH was a fantastic surprise find in the box, and I have since bought more individual bottles from my local warehouse.
Immediately upon opening the authentic Bavarian bottle, I smelled the light, sweet wheats and banana complex without having to search for it too hard.
The taste, again, was banana ,the icon of bavarian hefeweissen beer. Their use of it is perfect. It is a highlight of the beer, not the entire taste. There was additional spice notes that provided a strong finish. The entire bottle was great.
Highly recommend and worth keeping a few on hand at all times so you can introduce friends to it. 904 charactersroadies, Jul 14, 2012
