4.53/5  rDev +3%look: 5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5Been a while since I really drank a serious hefe, so I wanted to give one I knew was good a drink and a review. Drank this many times before, just now getting to reviewing it. Side poured with low vigor into a weizen glass. 
Appearance - I love the labeling and the history behind this brewery. Simple, old school, tells you right up front what you are getting. Pours a cloudy straw yellow color with a huge, dominating four finger pillowy head, looks like a cloud on top of the beer. Good lacing. Tons of sediments and carbonation inside the beer make this a top notch presentation.
Smell - Wheats, Breads, a little earthiness, but the primary smell was banana esters for sure. Powerful banana, fruit smell to the beer. Maybe even a little honey sweetness in there as well.
Taste - The heavy banana esters are still the primary favors, with a good secondary pop of cloves and a little spice towards the end as well. The breads and malts round out this beer. Very well put together, a very complete taste experience.
Mouthfeel - It's like eating a loaf of banana bread, drinking this. Big bodied, Thick creamy mouthfeel, big carbonation, excellent smooth finish. Hard to beat.
Overall - if you haven't had it, go get it and drink it. Excellent beer, almost unmatched in its category. Highly recommended, I will buy it and drink it again. There is a reason it is the top ranked hefe on all of BA. 1,400 charactersTheCondor, Jul 11, 2012
