4.38/5  rDev -0.5%look: 4.5 | smell: 4 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5Consumed 6/29/12
Appearance: Hazy gold - pours with a giant, fluffy white head, leaves blobs of lacing, retains a cap forever
Smell: Soft, bready wheat and yeast - bananas and cloves, in nice balance, in nice moderation - a touch of something lemony - nice malt base
Taste: Nicely balanced and stupidly, remarkably clean-tasting, refreshing - "refreshing" is a flavor, right? - mild banana, clove, and a touch of lemon, bubblegum - some straight-up yeast, with some yeasty spiciness - very mild bitterness - lightly bready malts, with some light graininess
Mouthfeel: Medium, but so smooth that it feels a bit fuller - nicely carbonated, refreshing
Overall: Beyond classic
This is a relatively simple beer, but it has great strength in its simplicity. The wheaty malt profile and the yeast come together in a remarkable way. The balance works better than any Hefeweizen I've ever tasted. Seriously. I should have had this years ago. 938 charactersangrybabboon, Jun 29, 2012
