Appearance: Yellow with orange highlights. Looks like a pineapple-orange juice. Moderately cloudy, but I see through the other side. Inspection with a bright light doesn't produce and visible particles, just lots of large bubbles calmly rising to the top. Moderate white head with yellow highlights. Good retention.
Taste: Glorious flavor. Grainy wheat followed by savory banana and mild orange citrus. Spicy clove and some black pepper phenols. Very little yeast. Some mild floral alcohol. Some mild residual white sugar. Some pine shows up associated with the hops and yeast at the aftertaste.
Mouthfeel: Medium body. Mild carbonation which is both creamy and stinging. Oily overall and finishes and bit dry.
Overall: Impressively savory and pleasant. Surprisingly bold considering the style and ABV. The best I've had. 918 characterssoulfly1492, May 01, 2012
