4.83/5  rDev +9.8%look: 5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 5Been saving this for Thanksgiving dinner and it was well worth the wait. Poured a beautiful dark honey/golden straw with plenty of haze and a 3 finger pillow white head that faded to 1 finger thorughout the beer. Lacing was spectacular and when poured into a weizen glass it stands out. Smell was very complex with notes of banana, cloves, lemon and bread. Not too strong, but adequate. Taste was fantastic. Follows the nose pretty close, but adds a hint of spices to balance the citrus/fruit on the front end. Classic for the style and spot on. Feel was a good bit of carbonation with a dry ending. Not too watery, but not overpowering. Overall- Not sure I can come up with anything new to say about this that hasn't already been said. This is the gold standard of a Hefeweizen IMO and easily in my top 5 all time brews. While I think nothing is perfect, this comes damn close. Complex/Full taste, great aromas, beautiful balance and a great top off to Thanksgiving Dinner. Will be gettting more of this for next summer- Outstanding! 1,034 charactersTheDinger, Nov 25, 2011
