4.45/5  rDev +1.1%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4 |  overall: 4.5Ok I have reviewed this beer on tap and now I’m returning to the bottled version, which is a beer I have drank for years and always loved. It’s not all that different in either iteration; I may actually enjoy this one a bit more from the bottle. Hazy light orange color. Huge fluffy white head that falls slowly with excellent lacing. Aroma is full of wheat and yeast, lots of the expected banana and clove notes, perhaps a bit lemony with some traces of coriander. 
The flavor is incomparable for the style: very pronounced bananas and cloves, lightly toasted malt, very low bitterness without much of a noticeable hop presence. A touch of sweetness. Lemony and yeasty. Crisply carbonated, light in body, extremely refreshing. I’ll take this one over a bland “summer” ale any day of the week. A true classic. 820 characterstobelerone, Nov 03, 2011
