4.5/5  rDev +2.3%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5Bottle enjoyed next to a NG Dancing Man Wheat. 
Pours a hazy golden color with a generous whitish head. Looks characteristic of the style. The nose is big wheat with suggestions of clove and banana. A touch of lemon. The taste is big wheat and present, but subdued clove and banana and lemon zing. Not the crazy amount of clove that sometimes comes out of these beers, nor a banana bomb. A bit sweeter and not as lemon/peppery than a lot of saisons and not as soda-like in the body, but not as sweet as a lot of Hefes. Really nice, easy drinking, balanced brew. Overall, this is a world class Hefe. 599 charactersseeswo, Oct 27, 2011
