4.97/5  rDev +13%look: 4.5 | smell: 5 | taste: 5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 5My first review here. 
Up until today, I had only ever had Pyramid as far as "hefeweizens" go. Blasphemy, I know. But considering that I hate that beer, I was skeptical to give others a try.
A: Pours a beautiful golden, hazy color with about 3 fingers worth of frothy white head.
S: Unbelievable amounts of banana and spices. Some citrus characteristics and a nice pungent scent that really has me aching to try this one.
T: Doesn't disappoint in the slightest. Tons of banana and clove pour out of this one. Front of the mouth it's all banana, middle of the tongue I get a nice kind of sour/pungent flavor, finishes with a nice yeast characteristic. Very, very refreshing. I wish I had another because I'd take it down in an instant. World class in my opinion. I didn't know hefeweisbier had potential like this. I'll be getting more of this soon.
M: Velvety. That's the best I can describe it. Nice carbonation, and a light body helps this one go down with ease. Very soft and smooth going down.
