4.43/5  rDev +0.7%look: 4.5 | smell: 4 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4 |  overall: 5Vigorous pour into a pint glass. Epic half-glass filling white fluffy-as-a-cloud head. Who knows how long this has sat on the shelf at BOTW, as I can't seem to find a date on it. The beer itself is a fairly cloudy pale yellow with a little tinge of caramel brownness. The head reminds me of a very proper rootbeer float "head", nice and fluffy, protecting it's inner goodness. This beer has superb head retention.
The nose is slightly of banana and clove, a nice warm bready scent in the background somewhere. Perhaps a little bubblegum? The notes really come alive as the beer warms (I served a little too cold).
Spicy and well balanced to taste. Only a little real hint of banana in this, cloves and other spices are at the forefront of this one. A little bit of breadiness as well.
The mouthfeel of this is a little on the watery side, like most hefe's I've tried.
The finish is short and refreshing, a nice dry finish that leaves you wanting to search the cellar/fridge for another bottle.
Drinkability on this is excellent. Probably one of the finest hefe's I've ever had, and I'm a fan. 1,097 charactersxenolithic, Jan 11, 2009
