4.8/5  rDev +9.1%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 5An exceptional hefeweizen. This beer is the gold standard for the style. It is well ahead of the competition in a very competitive German style with many great beers that probably date back for hundreds of years. The beer looks great. It's glowing, dusky, cloudy gold with a fine, soapy, craggy head. Lacing is in abundance. The smell is clean wheat spice, lots of fruity esters and sweet malt. The flavor is like drinking a bit of summer. You can taste the sunshine on the wheat fields when you take a sip of this beer. There's a ton of wheat spice and everything comes through crisply and cleanly but never bitingly. It is refreshing and cooling but also lush and full. The feel is velvety with lots of gentle suds. It is one of the best beers in the world and possibly the best beer in the world that could be considered a session beer, properly. 849 characterspopery, Dec 27, 2008
