Flavor is mild, creamy, delicious. Big yeast flavors with that lemon background, clove spicing is delicately managed. Crisp carbonation and just enough balancing hops keep everything in check. Finish is biscuity and maybe a little nutty. 
Body is thin, a little bit of watery character that is par for the course with a beer this fruity, flavorful, and quenching. This is the perfect example of a hefeweizen that I would return to again and again. 714 charactersBretSikkink, Jul 04, 2007
