4.6/5  rDev +4.5%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 5Appearance - Golden color with a slight haze. An ample white head that forms upon pour. A lively carbonation keeps feeding the head that resolves after a few minutes to a half-finger remain. Note the beer's color, carbonation, head and its retention. Is it clear or cloudy? Does it look lackluster and dull or alive and inviting?
Smell - Malty sweet aroma with a bit of a grassy presence as well. A bit of a yeasty nose as well. 
Taste - For a hefe, this is one of the more dense one's I've tasted. I would almost compare this with even a Belgian strong dark ale, it's that rich of a body. Very smooth with a dry finish. Very well balanced with just a bit of a hop bite at the end. 
