4.3/5  rDev -2.3%look: 4 | smell: 4 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4 |  overall: 4.5From the standard 12 oz. bottle, slender.
A - light golden, slightly hazy. Head is bright white and sustainable the whole way. Little lacing. Your classic Bavarian wheat appearance.
S - mixture of spices, pepper, allspice, clove. Little bit of spicy hop aroma in there too. Light, toasted wheat, bready.
T - wow, my tongue is excited. All sorts of bright, light spicy and fruity flavors. Clove, spicy banana, allspice, hints of anise. Yum. Mixed in are the firm bready, yeast flavors and toasty wheat. Dry, slightly bitter finish with spicy German noble hop flavors.
M - light, but not what I would call thin bodied. Carbonation is on the high side, per the style. Dry and not sweet.
D - I'm normally not a huge wheat beer fan, but this one is off the charts yummy. Perfect summer brew, light, refreshing. Amazing balance of spicy flavors, malt backbone, and firm bitterness. Make this your first hefe. 917 charactersgbarron, Jun 04, 2006
