1 pint bottle	
This beer poured a yellow color from the bottle that was cloudy, which I expected, but when held up I could see the carbonation bubbles, which were plenty. The head that was created was white in color, foamy, dense and long lasting. I you drank while it was freshly poured you would get the milk mustache. I really left no lace behind, just in spots but it seemed watery more then sticky. The aromas that came from the glass were of dough, citrus  lemons, floral hops, malt, wheat and barley grains, and I detected a small, small hint of metallic. The tastes that came from the beer were of floral hops, grains wheat and barley, citrus  lemons, sweet malt, dough, light nuts and spices and a small hint of alcohol. A very good beer and enjoyed it immensely. A great summer time beer, refreshing. Probably one of the best examples of this style that I have had so far. 952 charactersJarod, May 03, 2003
